Hi, 
I would like to share something that took me time to figure out.

Accidentals get aligned correctly and do not collide when the FormatAndDraw() method is used, but if you have a grand piano staff, notes in different staves can not be aligned with the same x position using FormatAndDraw().
The solution to align the notes is to not use FormatAndDraw(), but do it manually by creating voices for treble and bass staves, formatting them with a formatter like shown in step 2 of the VexFlow tutorial and draw the voices. The important part is to **not join the voices.**
If you do it that way, the notes are now correctly aligned, but the accidentals are colliding with each other.
That is because within the joinVoices() method, something gets called that aligns the accidentals. 
Workaround:
**You have to call the joinVoices() method for each voice individually, not to join voices, but to align accidentals.
Then format treble and bass voices together to the stave, but do not join them together.**

``` javascript
//create a voice for treble stave and one for bass stave
var voiceTreble = new Vex.Flow.Voice({num_beats:timeSignatureNumerator, beat_value: timeSignatureDenominator, resolution:Vex.Flow.RESOLUTION});
var voiceBass   = new Vex.Flow.Voice({num_beats:timeSignatureNumerator, beat_value: timeSignatureDenominator, resolution:Vex.Flow.RESOLUTION});

//add tickables (you pass the notes (staveNotes) that you have created before
voiceTreble.addTickables(yourStaveNotesForTrebleStave);
voiceBass.addTickables(yourStaveNotesForBassStave);

//do this if you want to get beams (manually)
var beamsTreble = Vex.Flow.Beam.applyAndGetBeams(voiceTreble);
var beamsBass = Vex.Flow.Beam.applyAndGetBeams(voiceBass);

var formatter = new Vex.Flow.Formatter();   //create a formatter

//joinVoices is the method which invokes something that renders the accidentals in the right way without colliding, but enter only one voice at a time for aligning the accidentals. You don't want to really join the voices
formatter.joinVoices([voiceTreble]);   
formatter.joinVoices([voiceBass]); 

//now align the voices to fit the grand piano staff. They are put in the array all together, but they are not joined together. In the second argument, you enter only the treble stave as stave here, assuming the bass stave and the treble stave have the same width as they are a grand piano staff
formatter.formatToStave([voiceTreble, voiceBass],yourTrebleStave, {align_rests: true});

var max_x = Math.max(yourTrebleStave.getNoteStartX(), yourBassStave.getNoteStartX());
yourTrebleStave.setNoteStartX(max_x);
yourBassStave.setNoteStartX(max_x);

//draw voices and beams, ctx is the context you got from your CANVAS / SVG
voiceTreble.draw(ctx, yourTrebleStave);
voiceBass.draw(ctx, yourBassStave);

if (beamsTreble != null) {
  for (var i=0; i<beamsTreble.length; ++i) {
    beamsTreble[i].setContext(ctxMain).draw();
  }
}
if (beamsBass != null) {
  for (var i=0; i<beamsBass.length; ++i) {
    beamsBass[i].setContext(ctxMain).draw();
  }
}
```

